title: GalaxyCV
description: Replicated and fine-tuned a VGG16 convolutional neural network to classify galaxies based on their morphological class using 17,000 images taken by the James Webb Space Telescope. Set up docker container with GPU integration to improve project replicabiity and reduce training times. Increased model accuracy by 10% from baseline neural network by fine-tuning the mode and performing data preprocessing.

title: Recipe Rating Prediction
description: Analyzed features including recipe descriptions, nutritional information, and preparation time to identify key predictors of user ratings. Performed missing data analysis to determine if features are not missing at random. Conducted a fairness analysis to evaluate model performance on vegetarian and non-vegetarian recipes.

title: Boston City Bike Station Visualization
description: Created an interactive visualization showcasing the use of rental bike stations at different periods of the day. The visualization is focused on the Boston Metropolitan Area and uses ds3 along with MapBox.
